 By Rasheed Sobowale Spanish professional tennis player, Rafael Nadal, beats Russian Daniil Medvedev 7-5, 6-3, 5-7, 4-6, 6-4 to win the 2019 US Open final; thus securing his 19th grand slam title. Nadal is a spot behind Roger Federer in the world ranking of men with the most major title. Roger Federer has won in total, 20 grand slam titles while Nadal has won 19 including his recently won US Open title. Medvedev is 23-year-old and married to Daria, his long-time girlfriend in September 12, 2018. Continue reading Breaking: Nadal defeats Medvedev to win US Open at Vanguard News. Source: Vanguard